# Gopher-Code: Go Library Stack

Complete library mapping for building gopher-code — Go equivalent of Claude Code.
Cross-referenced against TypeScript (original), Rust (claw-code-rust), and Python (claudecode) implementations.

---

## Core / Stdlib (Zero Dependencies)

| Category | Package | Purpose | Equivalent In |
|---|---|---|---|
| JSON | `encoding/json` | Serialization, streaming decoder, struct tags | TS: native JSON, Rust: serde_json, Python: json |
| Process Exec | `os/exec` | BashTool — subprocess with timeout via `CommandContext` | TS: child_process, Rust: std::process, Python: subprocess |
| Context | `context` | Cancellation/timeout propagation through query loop → provider → tools | TS: AbortController, Rust: CancellationToken, Python: asyncio |
| Logging | `log/slog` | Structured logging with levels | TS: custom, Rust: tracing, Python: logging |
| HTTP Client | `net/http` | Anthropic API calls, SSE stream reading | TS: axios, Rust: reqwest, Python: httpx |
| File I/O | `os`, `io`, `bufio` | FileReadTool, FileWriteTool — file operations with line numbers | TS: fs, Rust: std::fs, Python: pathlib |
| Path Handling | `path/filepath` | Path resolution, traversal prevention, `filepath.WalkDir` | TS: path, Rust: std::path, Python: pathlib |
| Regex | `regexp` | GrepTool fallback — safe finite automaton (no backtracking) | TS: RegExp, Rust: regex, Python: re |
| Sync | `sync` | Mutex, WaitGroup, Once — concurrent tool execution safety | TS: N/A, Rust: Arc<Mutex<T>>, Python: asyncio.Lock |
| Strings | `strings` | FileEditTool — Count (uniqueness check) + Replace | TS: String methods, Rust: str methods, Python: str methods |
| Testing | `testing` | Test framework — subtests via `t.Run`, `t.Parallel`, `-race` | TS: jest, Rust: #[test], Python: pytest |
| Signal | `os/signal` | `signal.NotifyContext` — Ctrl+C → context cancellation | TS: process.on('SIGINT'), Rust: tokio::signal, Python: signal |
| Embed | `embed` | Embed system prompts, default configs at compile time | TS: bundled strings, Rust: include_str!, Python: importlib.resources |

---

## Semi-Stdlib (golang.org/x/)

| Category | Package | Purpose | Equivalent In |
|---|---|---|---|
| Concurrency | `golang.org/x/sync/errgroup` | Parallel tool execution with error propagation + `SetLimit(n)` | TS: Promise.all, Rust: futures::join_all, Python: asyncio.gather |
| Terminal | `golang.org/x/term` | Raw terminal mode, terminal size detection | TS: process.stdout, Rust: crossterm, Python: shutil.get_terminal_size |

